cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.SI 

This paper is about improving spoken language understanding (SLU) in multi-turn dialogues by modeling inter-speaker relationships. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which includes research on natural language processing and dialogue systems. The paper also uses XLNet, a state-of-the-art pretrained model, which suggests it could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes new methods to improve SLU accuracy, which could fit under cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
